{"id":14881609,"mediaExerciseId":"991e8402-f3f7-4874-8c43-27672f52fc56","exerciseName":"11","chapterName":"17","chapterTitle":"Dividends and Payout Policy","groupId":612429,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":603,"solutions":[{"id":6001231,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"This exercise requires us to determine the homemade dividend in two years. ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":28,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/29041d58b0dc36ec42ed13be47ead43c/126bc8cfadf863c429924a3b55572d0c/lateximg_large.png","width":993},"regular":{"height":15,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/29041d58b0dc36ec42ed13be47ead43c/126bc8cfadf863c429924a3b55572d0c/lateximg.png","width":497}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"**Homemade dividend** is the amount of dividend per share that an investors determines to fulfill his objectives of cash-flow.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":68,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/29041d58b0dc36ec42ed13be47ead43c/db596e4d4a8fb0a60d70485e4600e3a0/lateximg_large.png","width":1010},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/29041d58b0dc36ec42ed13be47ead43c/db596e4d4a8fb0a60d70485e4600e3a0/lateximg.png","width":507}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"Homemade dividend is computed as follows:\n\n$$ \\begin{aligned}\n\\text{Homemade Dividend} &= \\text{ADP} - {\\text{RDP}}\\\\[1pt]\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nWhere:\n\nADP - Actual Dividend Price\n\nRDP - Required Dividend Price","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":234,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/29041d58b0dc36ec42ed13be47ead43c/a5e1fe88e115b267a9a76159503032f8/lateximg_large.png","width":740},"regular":{"height":119,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/29041d58b0dc36ec42ed13be47ead43c/a5e1fe88e115b267a9a76159503032f8/lateximg.png","width":371}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"Before we compute the homemade dividend, let's first identify the the actual dividend price by multiplying the share outstanding by the dividend price per share.\n\n$$ \\begin{aligned}\n\\text{ADP} &= \\text{Shares Outstanding}\\times{\\text{Dividend Price per share}}\\\\[5pt]\n&= \\text{1,000}\\times{\\text{\\$ 3.15}}\\\\[5pt]\n&=\\boxed{\\$\\hspace{5pt}3,150}\\\\\n\\end{aligned}$$\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":307,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/29041d58b0dc36ec42ed13be47ead43c/beb4b8d50e93f9e97926feffb352672e/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":155,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/29041d58b0dc36ec42ed13be47ead43c/beb4b8d50e93f9e97926feffb352672e/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"Now that we have computed the actual dividend price, we can compute now the homemade dividend using the equation in step 3.\n\n$$ \\begin{aligned}\n\\text{Homemade Dividend} &= \\text{ADP} - {\\text{RDP}}\\\\[5pt]\n &= \\text{\\$ 3,150} - {\\text{\\$ 1,500}}\\\\[5pt]\n&=\\boxed{\\$\\hspace{5pt}1,650}\\\\\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\n\nTherefore, the homemade dividend in two years of the company is **\\$ 1,650.**","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":357,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/29041d58b0dc36ec42ed13be47ead43c/0d1f5301caf46842b214cd6857fcc3ed/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":180,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/29041d58b0dc36ec42ed13be47ead43c/0d1f5301caf46842b214cd6857fcc3ed/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"1e8c2cda-c6ca-45a1-b670-3c253e34490c","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":5}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881610,"exerciseName":"12","page":603,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"90bd5958-d1fc-4745-a8dc-999344c9c5e0","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-17-questions-and-problems-12-90bd5958-d1fc-4745-a8dc-999344c9c5e0"},{"id":14881611,"exerciseName":"13","page":604,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"6a95e267-12f2-4c8f-9e5e-9fe17d31be7e","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-17-questions-and-problems-13-6a95e267-12f2-4c8f-9e5e-9fe17d31be7e"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14881608,"exerciseName":"10","page":603,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"78aa26bc-b143-4962-a0a5-1f923e59ecfd","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-17-questions-and-problems-10-78aa26bc-b143-4962-a0a5-1f923e59ecfd"},{"id":14881607,"exerciseName":"9","page":603,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"3833a51c-211e-444f-85cd-857dc2ddbde2","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanatio